  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Dice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>carrot</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/melty-sloppy-joe-sliders-gem-wedge-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Dissolve the <strong>beef stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>\n<p>Tear the <strong>mozzarella </strong>into large pieces</p>\n<p>Pat the <strong>torn mozzarella </strong>with kitchen paper, pressing down very firmly so that the mozzarella is nice and dry </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/melty-sloppy-joe-sliders-gem-wedge-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>vegetables</strong> have softened, add the<strong> beef mince</strong> with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/melty-sloppy-joe-sliders-gem-wedge-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>mini brioche rolls</strong> in half</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>bottom halves</strong> to a baking tray and put them in the oven for an initial 3-4 min or until starting to brown</p>\n<p>Tip: cooking them first stops the sliders from being soggy! </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/melty-sloppy-joe-sliders-gem-wedge-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>beef stock </strong>and<strong> tomato paste</strong> to the pan and cook for 5-6 min further or until the sauce has thickened to a ragù-like consistency</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/melty-sloppy-joe-sliders-gem-wedge-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, top the <strong>brioche bottoms</strong> with the <strong>beef mixture</strong> (pile them high!) and<strong> torn</strong> <strong>mozzarella</strong></p>\n<p>Return the tray to the oven for 5-7 min or until the <strong>mozzarella</strong> is starting to melt</p>\n<p>Once the mozzarella has started to melt, top with the<strong> brioche tops</strong> and return to the oven for 2-3 min further – these are your<strong> melty sloppy joe sliders</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/melty-sloppy-joe-sliders-gem-wedge-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>mayonnaise</strong>, <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> and <strong>dried oregano</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>creamy dressing</strong></p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>little</strong> <strong>gem lettuce<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into quarters lengthways – these are your <strong>gem wedges</strong> </p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/melty-sloppy-joe-sliders-gem-wedge-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>melty sloppy joe sliders</strong> with <strong>gem wedges</strong> to the side</p>\n<p>Drizzle the <strong>creamy dressing</strong> over the <strong>gem wedges</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
